<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Defs>

  <!-- Universal category — every unique melee weapon lists it. Carries Odyssey's six generic
       ported traits (cosmetic / value / weight; no on-hit effect): Ornamental, Ugly, Lightweight,
       Cumbersome, plus the Gold/Jade inlays. Includes UMW_Lightweight, the universal alone-able
       trait whose adjectives guarantee every weapon can be named.

       These six are INTENTIONAL self-contained ports, not lazy copies — do NOT "DRY" them into
       XML inheritance (ParentName) from Odyssey's trait defs. Two hard reasons:
         1. Odyssey's trait defs carry no Name= attribute, so ParentName can't target them without
            first patching one on (à la AddNameToBaseMeleeWeapons) — reaching into paid-DLC
            internals with a hard load-order dependency. A future Odyssey rename/restructure →
            "could not find parent node" → the trait fails to load → it drops out of UMW_Melee →
            and if that ever leaves a category with no alone-able adjective-bearing trait,
            weapon generation THROWS. Self-contained copies can't break that way.
         2. statOffsets/statFactors entries merge by element name (see Verse.XmlInheritance.
            RecursiveNodeCopyOverwriteElements), so an inherited RangedWeapon_* stat could NOT be
            removed by override — only Inherit="False" drops it, which means restating the whole
            block anyway (= copy-paste, plus a fragile parent link). No DRY win.
       Two flavours, per file:
         • Re-pointed to melee stats — Ornamental, Lightweight, Cumbersome: Odyssey drives
           ranged-only stats (RangedWeapon_DamageMultiplier / _WarmupMultiplier) that are inert on
           melee, so these were redesigned onto MeleeWeapon_* stats. Each file notes its deltas inline.
         • Verbatim-equivalent — Ugly, Gold/Jade inlay: touch only category-agnostic stats
           (Beauty / MarketValue / forcedColor), so their values match Odyssey 1:1. -->
  <WeaponCategoryDef>
    <defName>UMW_Melee</defName>
    <label>melee</label>
  </WeaponCategoryDef>

</Defs>
